# React Frontend Conventions

## Settings & Configuration

All localStorage keys and default values live in `src/config/settings.js`. Never read from `localStorage` directly in a component.

```javascript
// ✅ GOOD
import { getEffectiveSettings, STORAGE_KEYS } from '../config/settings';

// ❌ BAD
const token = localStorage.getItem('arc_github_token');
```

## API Calls

All API interactions go through `src/utils/api.js`. Components never call `fetch` directly.

## Component Patterns

- Functional components only
- Extract reusable markup into a dedicated component (e.g., `StepRow`)
- Props should be fully typed or at minimum documented with JSDoc

## CSS & Accessibility

- Touch targets must be ≥ 44 × 44 px
- Interactive elements need `aria-label` when text is absent (e.g., icon-only buttons)
- Media queries required: `max-width: 768px`, `max-width: 360px`, `prefers-reduced-motion`

## Error Handling

API errors must surface a user-visible message. Never silently swallow a rejected promise.

```javascript
// ✅ GOOD
try {
  const result = await startSprintAnalysis(settings);
  setExecutionArn(result.executionArn);
} catch (err) {
  setError(err.message || 'An unexpected error occurred');
}
```
